The paper deals with the stability of low-rank matrix reconstruction, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of the $\ell_*$-constrained minimal singular value is a technique that is relevant to all of these fields, and the paper's focus on this particular measure suggests that it is likely to be of interest to researchers in these areas.
